1
00:01:05,232 --> 00:01:08,766
<i>Don Corleone,</i> I need your help.

2
00:01:09,444 --> 00:01:11,606
And not just to light a little candle.

3
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:19,828
My gift was to be able to persuade
people to give to the Holy Church.

4
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:25,788
Then Rome decides to put me
in charge of the Vatican Bank...

5
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:30,667
but I was never a true banker.

6
00:01:33,844 --> 00:01:37,929
Mea culpa. I trusted my friends.

7
00:01:39,391 --> 00:01:41,007
Friendship and money...

8
00:01:42,603 --> 00:01:45,594
Oil and water... Indeed.

9
00:01:46,231 --> 00:01:52,944
But these "friends" used the good name
of the Church to feed their greed.

10
00:01:54,406 --> 00:01:56,568
If money was lost...

11
00:01:57,868 --> 00:01:59,734
then I am to blame.

12
00:02:02,331 --> 00:02:07,076
If only prayer could pay off
our 700 million dollar deficit.

13
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:11,127
769 million...

14
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:22,302
The Church owns 25 percent
of a large corporation. Immobiliare.

15
00:02:23,352 --> 00:02:25,434
You know the one I mean?

16
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:30,014
Largest landlord on Earth.
Real estate worth six billion dollars.

17
00:02:32,736 --> 00:02:33,942
That's true.

18
00:02:35,155 --> 00:02:38,648
And the Vatican vote
is necessary for control.

19
00:02:41,244 --> 00:02:44,077
No, you're mistaken.

20
00:02:44,665 --> 00:02:47,498
This isn't a question
of one person deciding.

21
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:49,074
One deciding vote.

22
00:02:49,169 --> 00:02:54,881
This is like any other company.
We have directors and very old rules.

23
00:02:56,051 --> 00:03:00,136
The Pope himself
would have to approve you.

24
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:06,808
We've sold the casinos.

25
00:03:08,647 --> 00:03:11,480
All businesses having to do
with gambling.

26
00:03:12,693 --> 00:03:18,359
We have no interests or investments
in anything illegitimate.

27
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:25,782
The Corleones are prepared to deposit
500 million dollars in the Vatican Bank

28
00:03:25,872 --> 00:03:29,740
when Mr. Corleone receives
majority control of Immobiliare.

29
00:03:29,835 --> 00:03:34,671
Immobiliare could be something new.
A European conglomerate.

30
00:03:36,299 --> 00:03:40,463
Few families have control
of such a company.

31
00:03:43,807 --> 00:03:45,969
It seems that, in today's world,

32
00:03:46,852 --> 00:03:50,937
the power to absolve debt is greater
than the power of forgiveness.

33
00:03:53,483 --> 00:03:55,190
600 million dollars.

34
00:04:00,365 --> 00:04:03,574
Don't overestimate
the power of forgiveness.

35
00:04:05,704 --> 00:04:09,746
Don Corleone, this
deal with Immobiliare

36
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:12,245
can make you
one of the richest men in the world.

37
00:04:12,836 --> 00:04:15,794
Your whole past history,
and the history of your family,

38
00:04:15,881 --> 00:04:19,545
and your children,
would be washed away.

39
00:04:22,387 --> 00:04:23,923
600 million.

40
00:04:40,822 --> 00:04:43,985
<i>The only wealth
in this world is children.</i>

41
00:04:44,117 --> 00:04:46,984
<i>More than all the money
and power on earth,</i>

42
00:04:48,246 --> 00:04:50,578
<i>you are my treasure.</i>

43
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:56,369
<i>Although I entrusted your education to
your mother for your own best interest,</i>

44
00:04:56,463 --> 00:05:01,799
<i>I look forward to seeing you, and to
a new period of harmony in our lives.</i>

45
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:07,213
<i>Perhaps you might prevail upon your
mother to come to this celebration.</i>

46
00:05:54,104 --> 00:05:56,766
Vincent, our name is not on the list.

47
00:05:59,401 --> 00:06:03,395
Write it in. Mancini. M-A-N-C-I-N-I.

48
00:06:05,282 --> 00:06:07,649
- Problem?
- My name isn't on the list.

49
00:06:07,742 --> 00:06:12,532
- Then you have to leave immediately.
- You want to dance with me?

50
00:06:12,622 --> 00:06:15,990
Joe, it's Vinnie. These are our guests.

51
00:06:16,084 --> 00:06:17,995
I'm sorry. I'm sorry, sir.

52
00:06:18,086 --> 00:06:20,327
Welcome to the party.

53
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:13,006
- It's good to see you.
- Good to see you. This is my husband.

54
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:15,386
- Sit down.
- My son, Anthony.

55
00:07:16,227 --> 00:07:21,313
The Order of Saint Sebastian is one of
the highest honors the Church awards.

56
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:23,982
It was first granted by Pope...

57
00:07:24,069 --> 00:07:27,232
What about Mr. Corleone's connections
with gambling?

58
00:07:27,739 --> 00:07:29,400
The press kits have...

59
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:31,823
What about his involvement
with the underworld?

60
00:07:31,910 --> 00:07:33,275
Cut the crap.

61
00:07:34,079 --> 00:07:36,912
The Pope, the Holy Father himself,

62
00:07:36,998 --> 00:07:41,583
has today blessed Michael Corleone.
Do you know better than the Pope?

63
00:07:42,837 --> 00:07:45,795
Vincent! She loves you.

64
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,338
Yeah?

65
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:52,799
I love you too.

66
00:07:59,104 --> 00:08:02,062
Hi, Vincent. I remember you.

67
00:08:03,858 --> 00:08:07,852
- From where?
- The last party we were at together.

68
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:11,029
- Did you come to the club?
- No, it was a wedding.

69
00:08:13,618 --> 00:08:16,201
I was eight and you were 15.

70
00:08:16,955 --> 00:08:19,947
I had many girlfriends when I was 15.

71
00:08:20,041 --> 00:08:22,248
- Eight-year-olds?
- Especially them.

72
00:08:24,629 --> 00:08:26,711
Where's Mary?

73
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:31,383
Would somebody please hail Mary?
Excuse me, Your Excellency.

74
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:36,005
You haven't kissed me hello yet.
Relatives always kiss.

75
00:08:36,099 --> 00:08:39,558
- Now we're related?
- I'm your little cousin.

76
00:08:47,569 --> 00:08:50,607
- Who's your father?
- I'll give you a hint.

77
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,655
He's Italian.

78
00:08:53,742 --> 00:08:57,451
Mary, we've been waiting for you.

79
00:08:57,537 --> 00:09:01,576
Remember to keep your voice low.

80
00:09:01,666 --> 00:09:04,158
And smile. Don't forget to smile.

81
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:18,547
Daddy, I'm so nervous.

82
00:09:24,439 --> 00:09:28,057
The honorary chairman of
the Vito Corleone Foundation,

83
00:09:28,735 --> 00:09:31,067
my daughter, Mary Corleone.

84
00:09:40,872 --> 00:09:42,203
Thanks.

85
00:09:43,750 --> 00:09:48,665
I think I inherited my father's love
for speechmaking. Here it goes.

86
00:09:50,215 --> 00:09:54,800
The Vito Corleone Foundation helps
the poor in every country,

87
00:09:54,886 --> 00:09:59,346
gives grants to artists,
funds medical research,

88
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:03,892
and is particularly dedicated
to the resurrection of Sicily.

89
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:06,724
Archbishop Gilday,

90
00:10:06,815 --> 00:10:11,901
here is 100 million dollars for the poor
of Sicily, in the name of Vito Corleone.

91
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:16,147
Don't spend it all in one place.

92
00:10:34,008 --> 00:10:39,299
Mary, I'm so proud of you.

93
00:10:46,354 --> 00:10:48,061
Michael...

94
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:50,981
You've done a wonderful thing
for Sicily.

95
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:55,524
Let's hope that the money gets
to the people who need it.

96
00:10:55,613 --> 00:10:56,853
Amen.

97
00:10:56,948 --> 00:11:02,068
The most important part:
Johnny Fontane!

98
00:11:10,879 --> 00:11:13,917
Thank you very much.
I'm happy to be here.

99
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:19,093
I would like you to join me in honoring
Commendatore Michael Corleone.

100
00:11:23,892 --> 00:11:27,226
I have something special
for our godfather.

101
00:11:27,312 --> 00:11:31,601
I happen to know his favorite song.
Michael, where are you going?

102
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:35,355
I'm off to the kitchen
to hear some Tony Bennett records.

103
00:11:37,030 --> 00:11:39,488
Your favorite song, "Salsiccia's Own".

104
00:11:39,574 --> 00:11:42,692
I'm having a salsiccia sandwich.
I'll be back.

105
00:12:17,195 --> 00:12:18,651
Hello, Kay.

106
00:12:29,082 --> 00:12:31,995
Congratulations, Michael.
That's quite an honor.

107
00:12:32,085 --> 00:12:35,077
But a little expensive,
wouldn't you say?

108
00:12:37,924 --> 00:12:40,916
- Cake?
- No, thank you.

109
00:12:54,816 --> 00:12:58,104
- It's been a long time, hasn't it?
- Yeah.

110
00:12:58,194 --> 00:13:00,105
- Eight years.
- Yeah.

111
00:13:00,947 --> 00:13:02,733
You look wonderful.

112
00:13:06,369 --> 00:13:10,988
Your son has something he wants to
talk to you about. I came here for him.

113
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:51,241
- What's wrong with being a lawyer?
- He wants his life to be in music.

114
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:57,417
Music is great, I love music.
But he should finish what he started.

115
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:58,868
Anthony...

116
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:01,914
- I'm going my own way.
- Your own way?

117
00:14:02,925 --> 00:14:04,757
- Professional singer?
- Yes.

118
00:14:04,844 --> 00:14:07,711
What happens if you fail?

119
00:14:07,805 --> 00:14:11,343
- I won't fail.
- Men always believe that.

120
00:14:12,435 --> 00:14:15,644
A law degree is like
taking out insurance.

121
00:14:16,397 --> 00:14:20,265
- After that you can work for me...
- I will never work for you.

122
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:23,401
I have bad memories.

123
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:27,610
Every family has bad memories.

124
00:14:31,454 --> 00:14:35,539
I'll always be your son, but won't have
anything to do with your business.

125
00:14:38,503 --> 00:14:42,212
Anthony... finish the law degree.

126
00:14:43,549 --> 00:14:44,710
No.

127
00:15:02,193 --> 00:15:06,152
Well, that he got from you. That "no".

128
00:15:09,117 --> 00:15:14,237
- You could've helped me convince him.
- Convince him of what?

129
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,154
Of what?

130
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,535
He throws his life away.

131
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:21,705
He throws greatness away.

132
00:15:22,797 --> 00:15:24,458
This is greatness?

133
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:30,427
Now that you're so respectable,
you're more dangerous than ever.

134
00:15:30,513 --> 00:15:34,632
I preferred you when you were
just a common Mafia hood.

135
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,050
Okay.

136
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:41,563
- Can we talk common sense here?
- All right.

137
00:15:48,489 --> 00:15:50,981
Tony knows that you killed Fredo.

138
00:15:57,707 --> 00:16:01,120
- What did you come here for?
- To protect my son.

139
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:06,125
Not to see you disguised by your church.
That was a shameful ceremony.

140
00:16:10,845 --> 00:16:13,257
I spent my life protecting my son.

141
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:17,549
I spent my life protecting my family!

142
00:16:17,643 --> 00:16:19,634
Let's be reasonable, okay?

143
00:16:20,855 --> 00:16:25,315
That's your big thing, isn't it,
Michael? Reason,

144
00:16:26,277 --> 00:16:29,736
- backed up by murder.
- Oh, God.

145
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:34,741
- You hate me. You hate me.
- No.

146
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:36,534
I don't hate you.

147
00:16:38,706 --> 00:16:40,322
I dread you.

148
00:16:44,212 --> 00:16:50,174
I did what I could, Kay, to protect all
of you from the horrors of this world.

149
00:16:51,761 --> 00:16:53,923
But you became my horror.

150
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:07,107
The children still love you, though.
Especially Mary.

151
00:17:10,238 --> 00:17:11,899
That's something.

152
00:17:14,367 --> 00:17:17,905
We can build on that. For their sake,

153
00:17:21,916 --> 00:17:23,247
let's try.

154
00:17:23,918 --> 00:17:29,004
Only if you let Tony go free to have
his own life, away from you.

155
00:17:36,597 --> 00:17:38,304
I'll let Tony go.

156
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:42,383
Thank you.

157
00:18:17,138 --> 00:18:19,049
- Hi.
- Hi.

158
00:18:21,142 --> 00:18:26,433
You could hurt somebody with those.
Let me show you around.

159
00:18:26,522 --> 00:18:28,638
Can you get me an interview
with Corleone?

160
00:18:28,733 --> 00:18:33,193
No. I'm a relative, but I can't do that.
What else can I do for you?

161
00:18:34,697 --> 00:18:37,564
- Handsome, but useless.
- Oh, yeah?

162
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:40,571
- That's okay, I'll gamble.
- Do you like to gamble?

163
00:18:40,661 --> 00:18:44,450
Let's go to Atlantic City.
I'll show you how to gamble.

164
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:48,829
- How do I know what numbers to bet?
- Do I look like a guy who's gonna lose?

165
00:18:49,462 --> 00:18:50,668
Well...

166
00:18:53,341 --> 00:18:55,252
Spooky-looking guy there.

167
00:18:56,093 --> 00:19:00,929
- What's a guy like that doing here?
- That's Joey Zasa's bulldog.

168
00:19:01,015 --> 00:19:03,097
- You know him?
- Yeah, I do.

169
00:19:04,060 --> 00:19:08,475
His name is Anthony Squigilaro.
They call him "The Ant".

170
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:11,602
He dips his bullets in cyanide.

171
00:19:20,493 --> 00:19:22,075
Don Altobello.

172
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:27,038
- I've come to pay my respects.
- <i>Grazie.</i>

173
00:19:30,544 --> 00:19:33,002
You honor my father's friendship.

174
00:19:33,089 --> 00:19:35,171
Where is my goddaughter?

175
00:19:37,051 --> 00:19:39,213
- Constanza!
- Don Altobello.

176
00:19:39,762 --> 00:19:44,256
It was not so long ago
that I held you in these old hands.

177
00:19:52,775 --> 00:19:57,941
Michael, I've lost all the venom,
all the juice of youth.

178
00:19:58,030 --> 00:20:03,241
I've lost the lust for women,
and now my mind is clear.

179
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:10,283
My duty to God is clear.
I have a special favor to ask of you.

180
00:20:11,919 --> 00:20:18,757
Can I attach my name
to the Vito Corleone Foundation,

181
00:20:19,385 --> 00:20:24,471
so that you and I can be joined
in name and spirit?

182
00:20:27,059 --> 00:20:28,641
One million dollars.

183
00:20:30,146 --> 00:20:31,978
A lot of money...

184
00:20:34,692 --> 00:20:38,651
- Godfather.
- Don Altobello, you have such a heart.

185
00:20:41,615 --> 00:20:45,984
Come, let's go and sample
some of that old <i>vino.</i>

186
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:56,252
The Vatican knows nothing
about these shareholders.

187
00:20:56,338 --> 00:20:57,544
Good.

188
00:20:57,631 --> 00:21:02,501
I have a tendency to worry. We've
increased our position substantially.

189
00:21:02,595 --> 00:21:07,135
- Naturally, I worry.
- Stop worrying, we have an agreement.

190
00:21:08,142 --> 00:21:11,100
Good. How do you think
I got this gray hair?

191
00:21:11,187 --> 00:21:16,933
Two seconds... Thank you for your
contribution to the swimming-pool.

192
00:21:17,026 --> 00:21:21,236
We need your help on Sam Wallace's
candidacy for judgeship.

193
00:21:21,322 --> 00:21:23,905
- We can always use a good judge.
- Thanks.

194
00:21:23,991 --> 00:21:25,652
Andrew!

195
00:21:25,743 --> 00:21:29,702
My godson Andrew Hagen.
My brother Tom's eldest boy.

196
00:21:29,789 --> 00:21:34,283
He's been assistant to Bishop Breelan
for three years.

197
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:38,711
- Hopes to be assigned to the Vatican.
- Rome needs fine young priests.

198
00:21:38,798 --> 00:21:41,790
His mother Teresa Hagen,
Bishop Gilday.

199
00:21:42,676 --> 00:21:43,676
Honored to meet you.

200
00:21:44,386 --> 00:21:47,344
Mr. Corleone. Hi. Grace Hamilton.

201
00:21:48,682 --> 00:21:53,176
Vincent Mancini promised to tell you
about me. That maybe you'd see me.

202
00:21:53,521 --> 00:21:56,639
- Did Vincent Mancini call about her?
- No.

203
00:21:56,732 --> 00:22:01,226
- You promised to stay out there, twice.
- I know.

204
00:22:02,196 --> 00:22:06,030
Joey Zasa showed up.
He's waiting in the lobby.

205
00:22:06,116 --> 00:22:10,155
<i>He wants to personally
congratulate you. Show his respect.</i>

206
00:22:10,746 --> 00:22:15,707
- Do I have to see him?
- He says you're his <i>patron.</i>

207
00:22:19,004 --> 00:22:21,041
Hey, Vinnie!

208
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,669
- Who's your favorite aunt?
- You are.

209
00:22:27,388 --> 00:22:30,881
Today I'll talk to Michael
about your little problem.

210
00:22:31,684 --> 00:22:34,893
If you'd warned me,
I would have worn a better suit.

211
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:39,305
The Meucci Association has elected you

212
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:42,017
Italian-American Man of the Year.

213
00:22:43,904 --> 00:22:45,269
Meucci...

214
00:22:48,242 --> 00:22:49,482
Who's Meucci?

215
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:57,074
The Italian-American who invented
the telephone, one year before Bell.

216
00:23:00,921 --> 00:23:03,788
And this is the reason
you've come today?

217
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:12,255
I...

218
00:23:15,519 --> 00:23:17,806
I've got a stone in my shoe.

219
00:23:19,315 --> 00:23:21,773
A two-bit punk who works for me.

220
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:26,064
The one who thinks he's related to you.

221
00:23:28,449 --> 00:23:29,780
A bastard.

222
00:23:33,829 --> 00:23:38,118
He's here. Vincent Mancini.
He's at the party.

223
00:23:41,545 --> 00:23:43,035
Bring him in.

224
00:23:44,465 --> 00:23:46,957
I think it's good that we talk.

225
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:49,800
No, <i>grazie.</i>

226
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:53,591
I have a problem...

227
00:23:54,183 --> 00:24:00,475
and I want to find out if it is
my problem or your problem.

228
00:24:00,564 --> 00:24:05,604
Your business is your business. I have
no interests or percentages from it.

229
00:24:07,029 --> 00:24:10,192
Good. Then it's my problem.

230
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:18,996
Michael, you know Vincent Mancini.
Sonny's boy.

231
00:24:21,001 --> 00:24:24,119
- How are you, Mr. Corleone?
- How are you?

232
00:24:24,213 --> 00:24:28,047
- Good. How are you? Good party.
- You like it?

233
00:24:28,133 --> 00:24:31,296
- Yes, I had to sneak in.
- You're dressed for it.

234
00:24:36,100 --> 00:24:40,014
So, what's the trouble
between you and Mr. Joe Zasa?

235
00:24:42,231 --> 00:24:46,566
- Just trouble. I'll take care of it.
- That's foolish of you.

236
00:24:46,652 --> 00:24:48,313
Foolish of me?

237
00:24:48,404 --> 00:24:50,486
It's a little foolish of this guy,
don't you think?

238
00:24:50,572 --> 00:24:51,858
Right?

239
00:24:53,325 --> 00:24:56,568
- Right?
- Temper like his father...

240
